questions.questionText:
What will the visual layout look like for these three flex items?

```css
.flex-container {
  display: flex;
  gap: 16px;
  justify-content: space-between;
  align-items: center;
  background: #f0f0f0;
  padding: 16px;
  height: 200px;
}

.item-1 { background: red;    height: 80px; }
.item-2 { background: green;  height: 120px; }
.item-3 { background: blue;   height: 60px; }
```

What does this CSS produce?

```css
.flex {
  display: flex;
  width: 600px;
}
.box-a { flex: 1 1 auto; background: #ddd; }
.box-b { flex: 2 1 auto; background: #aaa; }
.box-c { flex: 1 0 auto; background: #666; }
```
All three items have content of 100px wide.
